Introduces students to the main health care system management principles. The development of Estonian health care system; organisation, legislation and regulation of Estonian public health and health care system would be studied. Performance of Estonian health care system would be analysed in the global context.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Develop basic knowledge on health care system management principles, get an overview of Estonian health care organisation and regulationsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student will be expected: - to know main health care management principles; - to explain aim and issues of main health care reforms carried out in Estonia and can analyse them in the global context; - to know organisation and legislation of Estonian public health and health care system; - can describe functions and goals of health care systems; - to be able to find and use different types of health information to evaluate inputs, processes and outputs of public health and health care system performance.
